  "description": [
    "Book Tells How British Can Talk U S Into War See Story on Page 2 and Editorial on Pace 20 By THOMAS L STOKES Sen Nye R N D has brought before the Senate a very frank analysis by a British writer of possible methods of enlisting the United States on Englands side in the next war The propaganda technique for the United States is part of a book Prop aganda in the Next War written by Sidney Rogerson It is one of a se ries under the general title The Next War edited by Capt Liddell Hart internationally known military au thority In discussing the book and putting excerpts into the record Sen Nye ex plained it was published last fall but that its circulation is now being stopped The copy to which he had access which he said is the only one in the United States was procured from the library of a university he did not name MAIN PLANK It singles out as the main plank of British propaganda the old demo cratic one Among other methods it recommends that leading literary lights be sent to this country to cir culate the English viewpoint across the dinner"
